Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.17,0:00:07.88,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}Like a cruel angel{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.13,0:00:14.77,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}Become a legend, young boy{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.98,0:00:30.57,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}When a blue wind{\c}{\i0}\N{\i1\c&Hffffff&}Knocks on the door to your heart{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.74,0:00:37.75,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}You just gaze back at me{\c}{\i0}\N{\i1\c&Hffffff&}And smile oh so gently{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.66,0:00:45.42,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}So eager for something{\c}{\i0}\N{\i1\c&Hffffff&}You touch so softly{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.75,0:00:52.76,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}Those innocent eyes{\c}{\i0}\N{\i1\c&Hffffff&}Know nothing of the fate that awaits{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.35,0:00:59.48,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}But one day, you will realize{\c}{\i0}\N{\i1\c&Hffffff&}That upon your back{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.77,0:01:07.23,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}You have wings{\c}{\i0}\N{\i1\c&Hffffff&}You can fly to the faraway future{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.24,0:01:11.74,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}The cruel angel's thesis{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.95,0:01:15.62,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}One day, you'll take off through a window{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.70,0:01:19.37,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}If your overflowing pathos{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.45,0:01:22.87,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}Leads you to betray your memories{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.21,0:01:26.80,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}Then embrace the heavens and shine bright{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.88,0:01:30.76,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}Become legend, young boy{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.93,0:01:34.93,style.default,,0,0,0,,I'm in your debt again.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.39,0:01:36.93,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}But you don't intend to repay it.{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.60,0:01:40.48,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}About the Intel they were pursuing{\c}{\i0}\N{\i1\c&Hffffff&}using the Freedom of Information Act...{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.18,0:01:43.40,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}I mixed in some fake items{\c}{\i0}\N{\i1\c&Hffffff&}to throw them off the scent.{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.85,0:01:46.32,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}The government is working on{\c}{\i0}\N{\i1\c&Hffffff&}legislation behind the scenes,{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.61,0:01:48.32,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}but that should be derailed soon.{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.69,0:01:52.74,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}Now, about that other project...{\c}{\i0}\N{\i1\c&Hffffff&}Do you want me to handle it?{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.36,0:01:56.33,style.default,,0,0,0,,No, judging from the files you sent,\Nit shouldn't pose any problems.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.87,0:01:58.74,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}We'll stick to the scenario, then.{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.67,0:02:13.34,style.default,,0,0,0,,Good morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.22,0:02:18.06,style.default,,0,0,0,,Morning...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.44,0:02:29.65,style.default,,0,0,0,,This is how you get the day started!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.07,0:02:31.44,style.default,,0,0,0,,Don't most people drink coffee?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.90,0:02:35.86,style.default,,0,0,0,,Ever since old times,\NJapanese people have had
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.99,0:02:38.53,style.default,,0,0,0,,white rice, miso soup,\Nand sake in the morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.74,0:02:41.29,style.default,,0,0,0,,-That's in {\i1\c&Hffffff&}your{\c}{\i0} case, right, Ms. Misato?\N-Why the attitude?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.41,0:02:45.54,style.default,,0,0,0,,Whose turn was it\Nto cook breakfast this morning?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.54,0:02:50.96,style.default,,0,0,0,,I think I know why you're\Nstill single at your age.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.42,0:02:53.17,style.default,,0,0,0,,Well, excuse me for being so uncouth.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.84,0:02:54.84,style.default,,0,0,0,,And being a slob.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.59,0:02:57.30,style.default,,0,0,0,,Okay, you've made your point!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.14,0:02:58.97,style.default,,0,0,0,,Thanks, I'm done.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.77,0:03:03.73,style.default,,0,0,0,,Are you really coming to school today?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.81,0:03:07.10,style.default,,0,0,0,,Of course I am.\NIt's for your future plans meeting.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.31,0:03:09.06,style.default,,0,0,0,,But you're really busy at work.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.15,0:03:11.73,style.default,,0,0,0,,It's fine, it's fine.\NIt's all part of the job.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.36,0:03:13.69,style.default,,0,0,0,,Your job, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.49,0:03:18.49,style.default,,0,0,0,,Hello?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.20,0:03:21.66,style.default,,0,0,0,,Hi! You didn't have to\Ncome all the way over.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.83,0:03:23.16,style.default,,0,0,0,,Sure, we'll be right out.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.70,0:03:26.33,style.default,,0,0,0,,Ms. Misato, please don't come\Nto the door like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.79,0:03:29.13,style.default,,0,0,0,,-It's embarrassing.\N-Have it your way.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.71,0:03:34.21,style.default,,0,0,0,,Good morning, Mr. Ikari!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.71,0:03:36.63,style.default,,0,0,0,,Bye, Ms. Misato! We're off to school!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.18,0:03:38.30,style.default,,0,0,0,,Have a nice day!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.51,0:03:41.72,style.default,,0,0,0,,Come on, let's get going!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.31,0:03:47.14,style.default,,0,0,0,,Snark, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.10,0:03:52.07,style.default,,0,0,0,,Well, I guess it's a good sign\Nthat he's finally loosened up.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.32,0:03:58.16,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}Ma'am?{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.24,0:04:01.24,style.default,,0,0,0,,He just left the apartment.\NMaintain security on him.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.92,0:04:15.30,style.default,,0,0,0,,Look, she's here!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.80,0:04:23.51,style.default,,0,0,0,,She's so hot! Who is she?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.72,0:04:24.77,style.default,,0,0,0,,Ikari's guardian?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.85,0:04:27.52,style.default,,0,0,0,,You mean a babe like that looks after him?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.60,0:04:28.44,style.default,,0,0,0,,Horny idiots.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.19,0:04:33.82,style.default,,0,0,0,,Is Ms. Misato great or what?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.15,0:04:35.40,style.default,,0,0,0,,You think so?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.48,0:04:38.53,style.default,,0,0,0,,All that, and she's Nerv's\NOperations Director! That's amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.03,0:04:40.11,style.default,,0,0,0,,You think so?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.16,0:04:44.95,style.default,,0,0,0,,It's a good thing for us that Shinji\Nis such a clueless baby, Kensuke.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.04,0:04:46.95,style.default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, he won't get in our way.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.91,0:04:50.96,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}Tohji and Kensuke don't know{\c}{\i0}\N{\i1\c&Hffffff&}how big a slob she is.{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.63,0:04:55.34,style.default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I wish I could land a woman like her!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.42,0:04:56.92,style.default,,0,0,0,,I think you'd regret it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.38,0:04:58.84,style.default,,0,0,0,,You are one dense dude, big guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.26,0:05:02.34,style.default,,0,0,0,,Right! We'll leave peace on Earth\Nin your capable hands!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.51,0:05:05.10,style.default,,0,0,0,,So you can rest easy,\Nknowing that Ms. Misato is in ours!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.52,0:05:10.85,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}Unit 01 has met target cooling values.{\c}{\i0}\N{\i1\c&Hffffff&}Proceed to stage two.{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.94,0:05:14.15,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}Peace on Earth, huh?{\c}{\i0}\N{\i1\c&Hffffff&}That's what the Evas are for...{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.61,0:05:17.15,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}But what are they?{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.73,0:05:20.61,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}It smells like blood in the entry plug.{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.11,0:05:22.74,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}So why do I feel so safe in here?{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.99,0:05:26.87,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}When it's all said and done,{\c}{\i0}\N{\i1\c&Hffffff&}I have no idea what's going on.{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.70,0:05:30.12,style.default,,0,0,0,,How are Unit Zero's\Norganic chest components?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.37,0:05:31.75,style.default,,0,0,0,,Badly damaged.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.08,0:05:35.59,style.default,,0,0,0,,We're making new ones, but it's eating up\Nwhat's left of our supplemental budget.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.67,0:05:39.67,style.default,,0,0,0,,Maybe things will get a little easier\Nonce Unit Two arrives from Germany.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.76,0:05:41.34,style.default,,0,0,0,,It might be just the opposite.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.42,0:05:44.30,style.default,,0,0,0,,Angel disposal operations up there\Nalso cost money.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.39,0:05:47.35,style.default,,0,0,0,,No kidding. This place is\Nalways strapped for funds.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.43,0:05:49.77,style.default,,0,0,0,,The fate of humanity\Nis riding on us, for Pete's sake.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.85,0:05:53.06,style.default,,0,0,0,,It is what it is.\N"Man does not live by Eva alone."
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.31,0:05:56.44,style.default,,0,0,0,,It takes money\Nto keep the survivors alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.52,0:05:59.69,style.default,,0,0,0,,Speaking of budgets...\NThe Commander is off at another meeting?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.78,0:06:01.74,style.default,,0,0,0,,Yes, he's en route right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.32,0:06:05.16,style.default,,0,0,0,,Things are so much calmer here\Nwhen the Commander is away.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.96,0:06:16.67,style.default,,0,0,0,,Excuse me. Do you mind if I sit here\Nsince we're traveling together?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.84,0:06:22.55,style.default,,0,0,0,,The revised budget earmarked for sample\Ncollection was approved without comment.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.97,0:06:26.55,style.default,,0,0,0,,The Council places a premium\Non their own survival.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.76,0:06:28.68,style.default,,0,0,0,,That goal loosens their purse strings.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.85,0:06:32.64,style.default,,0,0,0,,Yes, their argument was always\Nthat the Angels wouldn't reappear.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.85,0:06:34.44,style.default,,0,0,0,,One other piece of good news:
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.19,0:06:40.07,style.default,,0,0,0,,All council nations, minus the US,\Nhave approved funding for Eva-06.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.61,0:06:43.19,style.default,,0,0,0,,Well, it's only a matter of time\Nbefore the Americans sign on, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.95,0:06:47.16,style.default,,0,0,0,,They have a powerful aversion\Nto high unemployment rates.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.95,0:06:49.28,style.default,,0,0,0,,What about yours?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.45,0:06:51.49,style.default,,0,0,0,,We will take part, starting with Unit 08.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.58,0:06:54.41,style.default,,0,0,0,,Phase Two of the Buildup Plan\Nis still in effect, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.100,0:06:58.59,style.default,,0,0,0,,Mind you, there is still the issue\Nof us not having a pilot for it yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.09,0:07:01.34,style.default,,0,0,0,,The Angels have returned.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.13,0:07:04.51,style.default,,0,0,0,,Our only path forward is to defeat them.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.26,0:07:08.68,style.default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I would also rather not have\Na repeat of the Second Impact.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.68,0:07:14.06,style.default,,0,0,0,,Wait, you're saying the Second Impact,\Nwhen Antarctica was vaporized--
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.60,0:07:19.52,style.default,,0,0,0,,Yes. The textbooks say it was a tragedy\Ncaused by a massive meteorite impact,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.94,0:07:22.53,style.default,,0,0,0,,but the truth has a tendency\Nto be covered up.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.07,0:07:25.07,style.default,,0,0,0,,Fifteen years ago in Antarctica,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.15,0:07:28.74,style.default,,0,0,0,,humanity found a humanoid object,\Nthe first of what we call Angels.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.45,0:07:33.04,style.default,,0,0,0,,But while studying it, there was\Na huge explosion of unknown cause.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.100,0:07:36.12,style.default,,0,0,0,,That is the truth behind\Nthe Second Impact.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.75,0:07:39.17,style.default,,0,0,0,,So what we're doing here--
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.25,0:07:42.30,style.default,,0,0,0,,Is preventing the onset\Nof a probable {\i1\c&Hffffff&}Third{\c}{\i0} Impact.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.55,0:07:45.67,style.default,,0,0,0,,That is why Nerv\Nand the Evangelions exist.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.76,0:07:49.18,style.default,,0,0,0,,By the way, it looks like they're\Ngoing ahead with it tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.14,0:07:51.97,style.default,,0,0,0,,Understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.24,0:08:06.24,style.default,,0,0,0,,Good morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.74,0:08:08.07,style.default,,0,0,0,,Um, good morning, ma'am.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.49,0:08:10.78,style.default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to Old Tokyo for work.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.28,0:08:13.58,style.default,,0,0,0,,I won't be back until late,\Nso go grab something for dinner.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.49,0:08:15.50,style.default,,0,0,0,,Bye.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.79,0:08:18.16,style.default,,0,0,0,,Um... Yes, ma'am.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.96,0:08:27.63,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}DERELICT ZONE NO. 28\N(CITY CENTER OF OLD TOKYO)
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.39,0:08:36.56,style.default,,0,0,0,,It's hard to believe that this\Nwas ever called a bustling metropolis.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.81,0:08:37.81,style.default,,0,0,0,,We're there.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.27,0:08:42.44,style.default,,0,0,0,,Why are they doing this here,\Nof all places?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.98,0:08:45.65,style.default,,0,0,0,,So, is the SSDF involved in this project?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.73,0:08:49.40,style.default,,0,0,0,,The Strategic Self Defense Force?\NNo, there's no sign they're involved.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.49,0:08:51.49,style.default,,0,0,0,,That explains why they're\Ngetting away with all this.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.12,0:09:02.33,style.default,,0,0,0,,The Japan Heavy\Nand Chemical Industries Consortium
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.42,0:09:06.25,style.default,,0,0,0,,thanks you for taking the time\Nout of your busy schedules today
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.21,0:09:09.05,style.default,,0,0,0,,to attend this demonstration.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.18,0:09:14.89,style.default,,0,0,0,,You will all be invited to view\Nthe public trials from the control room.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.60,0:09:18.18,style.default,,0,0,0,,But if anyone has any questions,\NI will be happy to answer them.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.39,0:09:21.73,style.default,,0,0,0,,-Here!\N-Ah, the renowned Dr. Ritsuko Akagi!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.19,0:09:23.94,style.default,,0,0,0,,We're honored by your presence.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.31,0:09:26.61,style.default,,0,0,0,,May I ask a few questions?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.69,0:09:28.28,style.default,,0,0,0,,By all means, ask away.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.53,0:09:32.16,style.default,,0,0,0,,According to your presentation,\Nthe unit has an internal heat engine.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.24,0:09:34.62,style.default,,0,0,0,,Yes, that is its major feature.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.03,0:09:38.41,style.default,,0,0,0,,It is guaranteed to be able to\Noperate continuously for 150 days.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.20,0:09:42.17,style.default,,0,0,0,,I believe installing a reactor\Ninside a ground combat weapon
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.25,0:09:47.00,style.default,,0,0,0,,meant for close-quarters combat\Nposes too great a safety risk.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.50,0:09:51.55,style.default,,0,0,0,,It is more useful than a "decisive weapon"\Nthat can't even run for five minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.63,0:09:54.14,style.default,,0,0,0,,Remote operation poses issues\Nwhen faced with emergencies.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.64,0:09:57.85,style.default,,0,0,0,,We consider it much more humane\Nthan placing undue strain on pilots
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.93,0:09:59.93,style.default,,0,0,0,,and exposing them to\Npsychological contamination.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.27,0:10:02.39,style.default,,0,0,0,,Enough, already. You're causing a scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.48,0:10:04.06,style.default,,0,0,0,,And deliberate operator malfeasance?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.40,0:10:08.44,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}It's safer than a wildly dangerous\Nweapon that can go out of control
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.53,0:10:10.57,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}and go on a rampage\Nat the drop of a hat, I'd say.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.65,0:10:13.15,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}A weapon that can't be controlled\Nis utter nonsense.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.61,0:10:16.41,style.default,,0,0,0,,It's like hysterical women.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.74,0:10:18.20,style.default,,0,0,0,,There's no reasoning with them.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.79,0:10:22.83,style.default,,0,0,0,,That is why we have pilots and technology!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.91,0:10:25.38,style.default,,0,0,0,,Come now, are you claiming\Nthat science and the human heart
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.46,0:10:27.42,style.default,,0,0,0,,can keep those monsters under control?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.71,0:10:28.92,style.default,,0,0,0,,Are you serious?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.13,0:10:30.30,style.default,,0,0,0,,Yes. Completely.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.80,0:10:33.63,style.default,,0,0,0,,Nerv's reliance on something\Nas nebulous as the human heart
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.72,0:10:36.22,style.default,,0,0,0,,is what let that rampage\Nhappen on their watch.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.51,0:10:39.76,style.default,,0,0,0,,As a result, the UN was hit\Nwith a huge extra budget request.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.10,0:10:43.10,style.default,,0,0,0,,Money that could have fed\N20,000 starving people elsewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.52,0:10:45.94,style.default,,0,0,0,,Plus, even though it was\Nsuch a serious incident,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.06,0:10:48.23,style.default,,0,0,0,,its cause remains a mystery?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.73,0:10:52.40,style.default,,0,0,0,,One would hope that you would carry out\Nyour duties as the responsible party.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.49,0:10:56.11,style.default,,0,0,0,,Isn't it nice how Nerv\Nenjoys extralegal protection?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.20,0:10:58.91,style.default,,0,0,0,,You aren't held responsible\Nfor your failings.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.33,0:11:00.41,style.default,,0,0,0,,Say what you like,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.83,0:11:03.83,style.default,,0,0,0,,but only Nerv's main weapon is capable\Nof defeating the hostile entities!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.41,0:11:08.13,style.default,,0,0,0,,Are you referring to the A.T. Field?\NWe'll have that licked eventually.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.00,0:11:11.55,style.default,,0,0,0,,Nerv's reign won't last forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.84,0:11:15.09,style.default,,0,0,0,,NERV PARTY
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.30,0:11:20.85,style.default,,0,0,0,,Stupid! Jerk!\NThat obnoxious son of a bitch!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.56,0:11:24.98,style.default,,0,0,0,,They're just getting even with us\Nfor cutting them out of the action!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.35,0:11:27.77,style.default,,0,0,0,,I am so pissed off!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.48,0:11:31.57,style.default,,0,0,0,,Enough, already. You're causing a scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.19,0:11:34.78,style.default,,0,0,0,,He's tooting his own horn\Nand wants to be patted on the back.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.28,0:11:37.45,style.default,,0,0,0,,What a pathetic little man.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.53,0:11:40.16,style.default,,0,0,0,,But how did they even\Nknow about A.T. Fields?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.70,0:11:42.24,style.default,,0,0,0,,Our secrets are leaking like a sieve.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.33,0:11:44.33,style.default,,0,0,0,,The Intelligence Department\Nneeds to do its damn job!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.80,0:12:00.97,style.default,,0,0,0,,We will now begin\Nthe activation test of the JA.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.51,0:12:03.18,style.default,,0,0,0,,There is absolutely no danger.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.14,0:12:06.85,style.default,,0,0,0,,Observe from that window\Nknowing that you are perfectly safe.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.85,0:12:10.02,style.default,,0,0,0,,Ready for activation!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.27,0:12:12.73,style.default,,0,0,0,,-Begin test!\N-All power systems engaged!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.82,0:12:16.15,style.default,,0,0,0,,-Pressure values normal.\N-Coolant pump system shows green.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.24,0:12:19.78,style.default,,0,0,0,,-Control rods, full withdrawal!\N-Power has reached critical.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.11,0:12:21.32,style.default,,0,0,0,,Power output, nominal!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.62,0:12:22.62,style.default,,0,0,0,,Begin walking cycle!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.08,0:12:25.54,style.default,,0,0,0,,Walk ahead, slow! Right foot forward!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.62,0:12:29.04,style.default,,0,0,0,,Roger. Walk ahead, slow!\NRight foot forward!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.38,0:12:37.26,style.default,,0,0,0,,Balance stable! Power system shows green!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.34,0:12:38.17,style.default,,0,0,0,,Roger!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.51,0:12:41.51,style.default,,0,0,0,,Proceeding to left foot forward!\NSteady as she goes!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.26,0:12:48.10,style.default,,0,0,0,,It's actually walking. I suppose they\Ndo have something to brag about.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.98,0:12:51.81,style.default,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.90,0:12:54.69,style.default,,0,0,0,,This is strange.\NPressure inside the reactor is climbing!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.23,0:12:57.24,style.default,,0,0,0,,Primary coolant loop temperatures rising!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.11,0:13:00.66,style.default,,0,0,0,,Open valves. Inject moderators!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.74,0:13:03.32,style.default,,0,0,0,,It's not working!\NPump output is not rising!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.62,0:13:08.66,style.default,,0,0,0,,Damn. Power it down. Emergency shutdown!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.75,0:13:12.33,style.default,,0,0,0,,-Shutdown signal sent!\N-Signal not received!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.42,0:13:15.17,style.default,,0,0,0,,-Radio channel also dead!\N-Control has been lost!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.50,0:13:16.75,style.default,,0,0,0,,This can't be happening...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.48,0:13:34.02,style.default,,0,0,0,,This robot is just as big a jerk\Nas its creator.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.86,0:13:40.24,style.default,,0,0,0,,Abnormalities in pressurizer!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.36,0:13:41.86,style.default,,0,0,0,,Control rod mechanism fail!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.03,0:13:44.16,style.default,,0,0,0,,At this rate, there is a risk\Nof a core meltdown!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.12,0:13:46.53,style.default,,0,0,0,,I can't believe it...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.08,0:13:49.62,style.default,,0,0,0,,The JA's programming\Nis supposed to anticipate
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.75,0:13:52.87,style.default,,0,0,0,,and deal with any possible contingency.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.62,0:13:55.42,style.default,,0,0,0,,This situation shouldn't be possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.84,0:13:58.84,style.default,,0,0,0,,And yet we're looking at\Nan impending core meltdown!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.71,0:14:03.97,style.default,,0,0,0,,The only thing we can still do\Nis wait for it to shut down on its own.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.05,0:14:05.76,style.default,,0,0,0,,What are the odds of that?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.85,0:14:08.85,style.default,,0,0,0,,They're 0.00002%. It would take a miracle.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.22,0:14:12.77,style.default,,0,0,0,,I prefer desperate action over waiting for\Na miracle. Tell me how to shut it down!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.77,0:14:15.31,style.default,,0,0,0,,We've tried everything!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.40,0:14:19.82,style.default,,0,0,0,,No, I bet there's still a last resort,\Na command to wipe the whole thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.07,0:14:21.65,style.default,,0,0,0,,Give me that password.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.86,0:14:24.28,style.default,,0,0,0,,Total program deletion is top secret.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.57,0:14:27.16,style.default,,0,0,0,,It's not my call to make.\NI don't have the authority to tell you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.58,0:14:30.04,style.default,,0,0,0,,Then {\i1\c&Hffffff&}get{\c}{\i0} the authority! Right now!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.54,0:14:34.29,style.default,,0,0,0,,Yes, it's me. Get me Mr. Manda in Tokyo-2.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.37,0:14:36.13,style.default,,0,0,0,,Yes, the Home Ministry Director.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.29,0:14:39.92,style.default,,0,0,0,,Oh, you mean that.\NI delegated all that to Yasugi.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.00,0:14:41.01,style.default,,0,0,0,,Ask him.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.84,0:14:45.59,style.default,,0,0,0,,A decision that big\Ncan't be made over the phone!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.68,0:14:47.80,style.default,,0,0,0,,Can you send me\Na formal request in writing?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.18,0:14:51.22,style.default,,0,0,0,,Then if I get permission from\NMr. Yoshizawa, you'll approve?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.47,0:14:54.27,style.default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I have Mr. Witz's approval already.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.35,0:14:57.48,style.default,,0,0,0,,-Yes. Yes, thank you.\N-They're all passing the buck.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.02,0:15:00.94,style.default,,0,0,0,,Official orders are on their way.\NThis has to be done properly.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.40,0:15:05.32,style.default,,0,0,0,,That won't cut it! It won't do any good\Nif they come after that thing blows!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.33,0:15:12.04,style.default,,0,0,0,,Jet Alone is currently\Nheading towards Atsugi.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.75,0:15:16.33,style.default,,0,0,0,,We're out of time.\NI'm taking action on my own authority.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.04,0:15:18.04,style.default,,0,0,0,,No offense.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.67,0:15:21.59,style.default,,0,0,0,,Hello, Hyuga?\NI've worked things out with Atsugi,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.67,0:15:24.42,style.default,,0,0,0,,so send Shinji and Unit 01\Nover here with Type F gear.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.51,0:15:25.93,style.default,,0,0,0,,Right, it's an emergency.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.01,0:15:28.05,style.default,,0,0,0,,You'll never pull it off.\NForget it, Capt. Katsuragi.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.59,0:15:30.47,style.default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, how would you even\Ngo about stopping it?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.22,0:15:33.27,style.default,,0,0,0,,Up close and personal. By hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.14,0:15:37.56,style.default,,0,0,0,,Are you serious?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.94,0:15:38.77,style.default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.86,0:15:42.94,style.default,,0,0,0,,But the interior is already flooded\Nwith contamination. It's too dangerous.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.44,0:15:45.82,style.default,,0,0,0,,If this works, it will save everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.11,0:15:51.53,style.default,,0,0,0,,You'll be able to manually open the hatch\Nonce the command signal from us stops.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.62,0:15:53.58,style.default,,0,0,0,,You can get inside\Nthrough the backpack rig.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.25,0:15:56.37,style.default,,0,0,0,,"Hope."
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.04,0:16:00.13,style.default,,0,0,0,,That's the password for\Nfull program deletion.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.21,0:16:02.04,style.default,,0,0,0,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.43,0:16:10.97,style.default,,0,0,0,,Our target is the JA. There's a risk of a\Nreactor meltdown in the next five minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.43,0:16:15.68,style.default,,0,0,0,,So we can't let it come any closer\Nto a population center.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.85,0:16:17.35,style.default,,0,0,0,,-Hyuga?\N-Ma'am?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.44,0:16:21.48,style.default,,0,0,0,,Once you cut the Eva loose,\Nget clear and climb to a safe altitude.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.56,0:16:22.69,style.default,,0,0,0,,-Roger.\N-Shinji?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.77,0:16:23.61,style.default,,0,0,0,,Yes, ma'am?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.69,0:16:26.78,style.default,,0,0,0,,Run alongside the target\Nand put me onto its back.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.86,0:16:29.61,style.default,,0,0,0,,After that, try to stall the JA\Nany way you can.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.36,0:16:32.24,style.default,,0,0,0,,You're going inside that thing?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.78,0:16:34.54,style.default,,0,0,0,,-Right.\N-That's nuts!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.99,0:16:37.71,style.default,,0,0,0,,Trust me, I know.\NIt's our best shot, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.96,0:16:39.37,style.default,,0,0,0,,But it's too dangerous!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.92,0:16:43.54,style.default,,0,0,0,,Don't worry. Your Eva will be fine\Neven if it blows up in your face.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.92,0:16:46.09,style.default,,0,0,0,,That's not what I meant!\NIt's too dangerous for {\i1\c&Hffffff&}you{\c}{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.55,0:16:49.26,style.default,,0,0,0,,Well, we have to do everything we can.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.72,0:16:51.34,style.default,,0,0,0,,It wouldn't sit right otherwise, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.39,0:16:55.72,style.default,,0,0,0,,I have eyes on the target!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.23,0:17:01.44,style.default,,0,0,0,,Okay, let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.19,0:17:07.53,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}Eva drop zone reached!{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.90,0:17:09.49,style.default,,0,0,0,,-Release docking lock!\N-Roger.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.84,0:17:31.05,style.default,,0,0,0,,-We've caught up!\N-Less than four minutes to go!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.13,0:17:32.13,style.default,,0,0,0,,Grab onto it!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.85,0:17:44.44,style.default,,0,0,0,,Don't worry! Just set me up there!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.53,0:17:52.66,style.default,,0,0,0,,Ms. Misato!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.08,0:17:58.16,style.default,,0,0,0,,Be careful.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.71,0:18:05.75,style.default,,0,0,0,,Wow, that's hot! This doesn't look good.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.96,0:18:07.46,style.default,,0,0,0,,Stop, damn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.80,0:18:15.14,style.default,,0,0,0,,Ms. Misato, hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.76,0:18:18.76,style.default,,0,0,0,,This is it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.23,0:18:32.11,style.default,,0,0,0,,HOPE
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.90,0:18:36.12,style.default,,0,0,0,,"Error"? What's the deal?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.79,0:18:44.71,style.default,,0,0,0,,There's no other explanation.\NThe program's been tampered with!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.51,0:18:53.84,style.default,,0,0,0,,Reactor will hit prompt criticality\Nin zero point two!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.43,0:18:55.97,style.default,,0,0,0,,Control rods aren't activating!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.39,0:18:58.39,style.default,,0,0,0,,Here goes nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.20,0:19:17.70,style.default,,0,0,0,,Ms. Misato! Get out of there!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.16,0:19:21.12,style.default,,0,0,0,,Damn it, move! You piece of...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.54,0:19:26.42,style.default,,0,0,0,,Ms. Misato!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.84,0:19:33.76,style.default,,0,0,0,,Zero point one to prompt criticality!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.96,0:19:35.55,style.default,,0,0,0,,It's no use, it's going to blow!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.55,0:19:37.97,style.default,,0,0,0,,-We failed...\N-Ms. Misato!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.49,0:20:02.33,style.default,,0,0,0,,She did it!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.66,0:20:04.75,style.default,,0,0,0,,-Pressure down!\N-All readings normal!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.83,0:20:08.17,style.default,,0,0,0,,-We're saved!\N-She did it!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.25,0:20:10.00,style.default,,0,0,0,,She did it!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.84,0:20:11.67,style.default,,0,0,0,,That fool...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.38,0:20:14.09,style.default,,0,0,0,,Ms. Misato, are you all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.30,0:20:15.30,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}Ms. Misato!{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.55,0:20:18.38,style.default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, but I feel like crap...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.26,0:20:21.64,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}Thank goodness! You're okay, then?{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.14,0:20:24.93,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}Wow, that's great... What a relief.{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.47,0:20:27.94,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}You were amazing!{\c}{\i0}\N{\i1\c&Hffffff&}I was so wrong about you!{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.10,0:20:29.85,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}A miracle really did happen!{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.10,0:20:30.94,style.default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.44,0:20:34.23,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}But this little miracle{\c}{\i0}\N{\i1\c&Hffffff&}was arranged by someone.{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.03,0:20:40.36,style.default,,0,0,0,,Unit 01 has been retrieved safely.\NThere's no danger of contamination.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.03,0:20:44.29,style.default,,0,0,0,,Aside from Capt. Katsuragi's actions,\Neverything went according to scenario.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.37,0:20:45.58,style.default,,0,0,0,,Well done.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.34,0:20:57.34,style.default,,0,0,0,,Morning...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.10,0:21:07.60,style.default,,0,0,0,,Next up, a nice morning shower!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.02,0:21:11.19,style.default,,0,0,0,,Where did I leave my bra and panties?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.32,0:21:16.32,style.default,,0,0,0,,Good morning, Mr. Ikari!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.98,0:21:18.07,style.default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, good morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.49,0:21:19.70,style.default,,0,0,0,,See you later!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.78,0:21:21.16,style.default,,0,0,0,,Have a nice day!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.57,0:21:26.33,style.default,,0,0,0,,Ms. Misato is so cool...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.62,0:21:30.25,style.default,,0,0,0,,I thought so, too,\Nbut she's so embarrassing at home!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.33,0:21:34.04,style.default,,0,0,0,,She's sloppy, dresses like a bum,\Nand is a complete slob!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.46,0:21:37.38,style.default,,0,0,0,,Watching her act like that\Nmakes me cringe!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.63,0:21:39.59,style.default,,0,0,0,,That makes me extra jealous.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.55,0:21:42.55,style.default,,0,0,0,,How come?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.34,0:21:47.26,style.default,,0,0,0,,-You're such a baby, Ikari.\N-You said it!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.35,0:21:48.47,style.default,,0,0,0,,And why is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.72,0:21:51.31,style.default,,0,0,0,,That's the {\i1\c&Hffffff&}real{\c}{\i0} Misato,\Nthe one we outsiders never see.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.56,0:21:54.27,style.default,,0,0,0,,That means you're family.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.98,0:22:01.90,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}TO BE CONTINUED
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.43,0:23:08.26,style.default,,0,0,0,,NEXT EPISODE
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.26,0:23:14.56,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}Eva-02 and its pilot leave{\c}{\i0}\N{\i1\c&Hffffff&}Wilhelmshaven, Germany, for Japan.{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.77,0:23:17.52,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}The sudden attack of an Angel{\c}{\i0}\N{\i1\c&Hffffff&}forces the activated Unit 02{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.61,0:23:19.19,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}into Nerv's first underwater Eva battle.{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.27,0:23:21.57,style.default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\c&Hffffff&}Next episode! "Asuka Arrives in Japan!"{\c}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.23,0:23:25.49,style.default,,0,0,0,,Translator: Dan Kanemitsu\NSubtitle Editor: David Fleming
